# Draws a unit-distance embedding of the Heawood graph.
# Follows the first construction given in Gerbracht (2008),
# Eleven Unit Distance Embeddings of the Heawood Graph, https://arxiv.org/abs/0912.5395

# Files like this passed to drawgraph.py must eventually define two sequences,
# `vertices` (complex numbers) and `edges` (pairs of indices on vertices).
# Another scale parameter controls how big the canvas becomes.

# Fixed points in the construction
p5, l5, p7, l7, p2, l3 = mpf(0), mpf(1), mpc(1+1j), mpc(1+2j), mpc(2j), mpc(1j)
